=== Getting help if you use a starter kit ===

Some starter kits like [[Spacemacs]] and DoomEmacs have their own communities where you can ask for help. Ask those communities first before asking general Emacs community help resources because those starter kits modify Emacs behavior extensively.

For other starter kits, sometimes the author of the starter kit will be able to help if you have a specific question or suggestion. See the starter kit's page for any instructions on asking for help, or check the project to see if it has an Issues tab that is pretty active.

If you can't find help that way, then reach out to other Emacs help resources (GetHelp). Make sure to mention which starter kit you're using, how you've modified it, and what you want to do. This is because starter kits can modify a lot of Emacs's behavior, so it helps to ask people with experience with your specific starter kit.

